HEADWORD: Discumber
<hw>Dis*cum"ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>cumber</ets>: cf. OF.
<ets>descombrer</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from that which cumbers or
impedes; to disencumber.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
